HEADWORD: Relume
<hw>Re*lume"</hw> <pr>(r?-l?m")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Relumed</conjf>
<pr>(-l?md")</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Reluming</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OF. <ets>relumer</ets> (cf. F.
<ets>rallumer</ets>), L. <ets>reluminare</ets>; pref. <ets>re-</ets> re-
+ <ets>luminare</ets> to light. Cf. <er>Reillume</er>.]</ety> <def>To
rekindle; to light again.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Relumed</qex> her ancient light, not kindled new.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I know not where is that Promethean heat⟦br⟧
That can thy light <qex>relume</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Relumine</ent>⟦br⟧
